---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Nonprofit | PoliceConduct.org"
  pagePath="/partner/nonprofit/"
>
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">
              Nonprofit
            </li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">Data-Driven Change</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Data sovereignty and policy leverage for nonprofit and advocacy
              teams.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  Nonprofits and advocacy coalitions
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  Transform 2025-2026 transparency records into actionable
                  policy.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">1. The wandering officer tracker</h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
              Track officer careers across departments to expose systemic
              shuffling and support stronger decertification laws.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
              <li>
                Aggregate reports tied to officer movement between precincts.
              </li>
              <li>Document resignation-during-investigation patterns.</li>
              <li>Support evidence-backed policy demands for state reforms.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Advocacy win</div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Use verified movement data to show city leadership that the
                  problem is systemic, not anecdotal.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Building social license and public trust
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Evidence-based reporting shifts the narrative from anecdotes to
          procedural justice.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Aggregated data reports
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Move beyond anecdotes</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Provide data summaries like "90% of stops in this zip code
                  resulted in no citation."
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Policy leverage
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Harder to ignore</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Present statistical evidence of bias or inefficiency to
                  municipal leaders.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">3. Advocacy toolset</h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Feature</th>
                <th scope="col">Growth benefit for advocacy groups</th>
                <th scope="col">Impact for the community</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Community intake portal</strong></td>
                <td>Offer a trusted alternative to filing at the precinct.</td>
                <td>Reduces fear of retaliation for community members.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Pattern alerts</strong></td>
                <td
                  >Get notified about use-of-force or illegal search spikes.</td
                >
                <td>Enables rapid response and targeted legal support.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Verification loops</strong></td>
                <td>Collaborate with experts to validate reports.</td>
                <td>Boosts credibility for public statements.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Policy heat maps</strong></td>
                <td>Visualize where aggressive policies are applied.</td>
                <td>Guide education campaigns and outreach.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-start">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Community impact kit
                </p>
                <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold mb-0">Resource kit</h2>
                <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                  Tools that turn data into community action.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3">
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold mb-1">
                  Know your rights reporting guide
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Co-branded PDFs that explain how to document interactions for
                  advocacy use.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold mb-1">Public safety scorecard</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Automated department summaries based on reports and linked
                  public records.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold mb-1">Actionable metadata exports</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  De-identified data exports for deep-dive audits on
                  disparities.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">4. The 2026 data broker defense</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          As states roll out delete and opt-out platforms, public record
          exemptions and First Amendment protections preserve a permanent,
          searchable history of police conduct for your community.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div
          class="d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row align-items-lg-center justify-content-between gap-3"
        >
          <div>
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-1">
              Ready to build a community data partnership?
            </h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
              We can draft a proposal focused on wandering officer tracking or
              pretrial transparency.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
            href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20a%20community%20data%20partnership%20proposal%20focused%20on%20wandering%20officers%20or%20pretrial%20transparency."
          >
            Request the partnership proposal
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
